    "narrative": "Today\u2019s offensive engine is anchored by **Corbin Carroll**, who commands the highest score of the day at 87.14. Facing an extremely favorable matchup against Martin (4.68 xERA), **Carroll** benefits from a massive 17% SP Skill boost and a prime #3 spot in the order, making him our primary source for both counting stats and high-leverage stolen base opportunities. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** is in an elite spot against Waldron; the combination of a high-xERA opponent (7.83) and a massive 14% park factor boost elevates him to a 75.75 score. **Jose Caballero** remains a high-value play as well, with his dynamic platoon advantage against Tolle pushing his efficiency north of 64.0, further cementing his role as a staple for our speed-starved category goals.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Brice Turang**, who nearly cracked the lineup with a 45.53 score. Despite his elite speed, the brutal matchup against Skubal (2.71 xERA) effectively neutralized his upside, leading us to favor the raw power and park-adjusted scoring of players like **Kyle Karros** and **Giancarlo Stanton**. We are carrying several \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Jose Caballero**, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**; while our projections assume their spots in the order, these scores are sensitive to volatility. Owners should monitor weather updates for the Tolle/Ritchie matchups, but as it stands, we are prioritizing the high-ceiling matchups against Waldron and the favorable park conditions for **Austin Riley** and **James Wood** to optimize our daily floor.",
